UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0929119917306181
KW  - Debt maturity
KW  - Short-maturity debt
KW  - Acquisitions
KW  - Cash holdings
KW  - Agency conflicts
AB  - We study the disciplinary role of short-maturity debt in cash-rich firms. We report evidence that such debt mitigates cash-rich firms' overinvestment in acquisitions. The disciplinary role is mostly concentrated among cash-rich firms that are weakly governed and have limited access to the public debt market and is also more pronounced for cash-rich firms that operate in less competitive industries. Furthermore, for cash-rich acquirers, high levels of short-maturity debt are associated with higher acquisition announcement returns and better post-acquisition operating performance. Overall, our results highlight the effective role of short-maturity debt in reducing agency cost.
